1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,420
Today, for all you viewers at home...

2
00:00:03,420 --> 00:00:07,650
I have some sad news to deliver.

3
00:00:09,650 --> 00:00:14,160
A part of our Gaki no Tsukai team,
ever since the second episode...

4
00:00:16,830 --> 00:00:22,300
Yamazaki has decided that he will be
leaving the show, as of today.

5
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:31,510
- Well, he said this was "THE END".
- Ah, I see.

6
00:00:37,520 --> 00:00:43,390
Well, let's bring the honored guess out.
I would like to introduce Housei Yamazaki.

7
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:59,550
Today is your last day, correct?
- Right. This is the end for me.

8
00:01:00,310 --> 00:01:06,340
But, there's a really gloomy atmosphere.

9
00:01:06,340 --> 00:01:10,550
- That's true, because what ever you did, there was always a joking air about it.

10
00:01:10,550 --> 00:01:18,260
In actuality, something like this has a
sad part to it as well.

11
00:01:19,620 --> 00:01:22,660
Like when we did the "5 Rangers" skits, you always had to be the Yellow Ranger.

12
00:01:24,710 --> 00:01:30,170
- Hmm? This was his choice.
- It was his choice, I guess.

13
00:01:30,170 --> 00:01:35,040
But neither Endo nor myself have heard any
reasoning behind you leaving.

14
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:40,010
Like, what kinds of things
made you decide to leave.
- I don't understand the reasoning behind it either.

15
00:01:41,820 --> 00:01:46,420
- Well, I managed to get a girlfriend.

16
00:01:46,550 --> 00:01:50,550
I just listened to her opinions some...

17
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:54,330
She watches the show all the time.
We're pretty deep in love.

18
00:01:56,620 --> 00:01:59,530
- But still, you wouldn't have
to leave, would you?

19
00:01:59,530 --> 00:02:03,550
- When you watch the way
I appear on shows...

20
00:02:05,170 --> 00:02:08,810
I'm always a talk show guest or something.

21
00:02:14,580 --> 00:02:19,420
I told that to the producers.
"I'd like to appear on a few
other shows", I said.

22
00:02:19,420 --> 00:02:23,530
He basically said, "That
might be impossible."

23
00:02:25,260 --> 00:02:27,530
"Might be impossible?"

24
00:02:29,760 --> 00:02:33,500
Why would he say "impossible"
so plainly, Yama-chan?

25
00:02:33,930 --> 00:02:38,500
- At that time, he probably wasn't thinking
about the best way to put it.

26
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:44,280
- Maybe you should have said
you weren't leaving...

27
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:50,370
- Right. Maybe if he'd added
"I'm okay here, but..."

28
00:02:51,320 --> 00:02:54,490
"No, it's okay. You can
do all sorts of shows."

29
00:02:55,040 --> 00:03:01,330
Then you could go all sorts of places.
- Because the "Yamazaki flower"
hasn't stopped growing.

