Now it's starting to feel like you're leaving.

99
00:13:36,530 --> 00:13:40,300
... Because of the older clips of you were funny.

100
00:13:44,150 --> 00:13:50,940
The show's producer, Mr. Suga, would like to give a parting message to you.

101
00:13:50,940 --> 00:13:54,150
Yama-chan, thank you for these 12 years.

102
00:13:54,860 --> 00:14:01,910
In 12 years, a lot of things can happen.
Things like aiming to be better than Downtown...

103
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:09,730
Back in Nihon TV's "Golden Days", I was choking on a pin.
I talked on and on about lots of different things, and was a pain in the neck for lots of people.

104
00:14:09,730 --> 00:14:19,140
From now on at Nihon TV, my new producer and I will work as hard as we can. Thank you.

105
00:14:28,330 --> 00:14:38,620
- And now we'll have a few last words from Yamazaki's show business juniors, Cocorico.

106
00:14:43,660 --> 00:14:47,730
- Mr. Housei, thanks for all your hard work.

107
00:14:47,730 --> 00:14:54,640
Before we came, it was you and Downtown here.

108
00:14:55,080 --> 00:15:00,710
